Jovetic made just 18 appearances for City in his debut campaign last term that was blighted by injuries.

The £22million signing from Fiorentina was restricted to just seven starts in all competitions as Manuel Pellegrini's side won achieved a Premier League and Capital One Cup double.

However, Jovetic's pre-season dedication seems to have paid off with the 24-year-old having started both of City's Premier League games this season at Newcastle and against Liverpool.

Pellegrini's faith in Jovetic looks to have been rewarded after he collected man-of-the-match for his two-goal performance in their 3-1 win against the Reds on Monday night.

